The paper deals with the problem of learning log-concave distributions, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithmic approach involves information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC), as well as techniques from probability and statistics (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential applicability of the approach to other distribution families, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
